TY  - JOUR
AB  - In a general equilibrium model with incomplete asset markets, nominal securities, and mean-variance preferences, a monetary union is desirable when the gain from eliminating excess volatility of nominal variables exceeds the cost of reducing the number of currencies with which to hedge risks.
